               <history>
                  <origin when="1473" when-custom="1784" calendar="Seleucid">
                     <origPlace> Turkmenistan (Merv)</origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Black round stamp of <persName>Yaʿaḳov Mahṿashef</persName> (<persName>Yakob Mavoshev</persName>) on ff. 1r, 269r and 270r:
									'<quote xml:lang="he">יעקב מהוושוף</quote> Якубъ Мавошевъ Г.
								Самаркандъ'.
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <persName>David Solomon Sassoon</persName> (1880-1942): collector of
								Jewish manuscripts: his bookplate on back pastedown.
                     </p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Acquired from the Sassoon collection, at the Sotheby's sale in
								Zürich, November 1978. Date of accession 30 November 1978. Paper
								slip glued onto front flyleaf (iii)r with notes regarding the repair
								of the volume.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
